              example: Game 1 has a control schema where reload is <strong>X</strong> and Game 2 has a control schema where reload is <strong>B</strong>. User 1 likes to map the action <strong>reload</strong> to their bottom-left-paddle. Now User one is getting used to bottom-left-paddle pointing at two different mappings. This can get more inconsistent once all paddles have been mapped. What Map-X does is keep the entire controller consistent throughout games which also keeps your paddles consistent
